The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                       The City Diary
                A Calcutta police team, headed by additional police commissioner (special) Rajeev Kumar, left for Delhi to discuss security arrangements following serial blasts in Delhi, home secretary Asok Mohan Chakrabarti said on Monday. He said that with Puja round the corner, vigil is being stepped up at shopping malls, multiplexes and other public places. Officials of the Calcutta Municipal Corporation are being consulted for security arrangement in pandals, Chakrabarti added.     Five persons, including two women, were arrested on Monday in connection with Sundays violence at Sonarpur station. Eleven people, including the inspector-in-charge of Sonarpur police station and two women constables, were injured. All the five are residents of Sonarpur.    Members of a club clashed with a trader and his friends in Kadambagachhi, Barasat, on Sunday night. Members of Balak Brinda had demanded a fan and two chairs from shop owner Sheikh Pintu Mondal for their club, police said. When five club members came for the promised items, some of Mondals friends beat them up. The club members returned with their friends and a brawl ensued. The club members also tried to obstruct train services near Kadambagachhi. Police and RAF personnel arrived and dispersed the mob. Three people were arrested and a police picket posted near the spot, an officer said.    Train services in the Sealdah south section of Eastern Railway was disrupted for two hours on Monday because of a demonstration by passengers protesting delay in train services.     A fire broke out in a cotton godown at Srirambhang Road in Salkia, on Monday. Five fire tenders brought the blaze under control.     A five-day Consumer Protection Fair was inaugurated at Netaji Indoor Stadium on Monday. Aimed at spreading awareness among people, the fair hosted a number of stalls selling various consumer items.                                                                                                                                                              
